<li id="cite_note-26"><b><a href="#cite_ref-26" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="web" id="CITEREFWright1999"><a href="/wiki/Canon_Kenyon_Wright" title="Canon Kenyon Wright" class="mw-redirect">Wright, Kenyon</a> (1999-04-04). <a href="http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_qn4156/is_19990404/ai_n13938013" class="external text" title="http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_qn4156/is_19990404/ai_n13938013" rel="nofollow">"Scotland can sing a new song to a different tune and in a clear voice"</a>. Sunday Herald<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_qn4156/is_19990404/ai_n13938013" class="external free" title="http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_qn4156/is_19990404/ai_n13938013" rel="nofollow">http://findarticles.com/p/articles/mi_qn4156/is_19990404/ai_n13938013</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2008-03-01</span>.  "... the Claim of Right of Scotland. I have it before me now as I write - a note of sadness as I see that the first two signatures, side by side, are those of the late John Smith MP and myself, a note of gratified surprise to see these closely followed by the autographs of Gordon Brown, Robin Cook, George Robertson, Donald Dewar, Malcolm Bruce, Jim Wallace and, more important, an impressive cross-section of Scotland's civil society."</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Scotland+can+sing+a+new+song+to+a+different+tune+and+in+a+clear+voice&amp;rft.atitle=&amp;rft.aulast=Wright&amp;rft.aufirst=Kenyon&amp;rft.au=Wright%2C+Kenyon&amp;rft.date=1999-04-04&amp;rft.pub=Sunday+Herald&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Ffindarticles.com%2Fp%2Farticles%2Fmi_qn4156%2Fis_19990404%2Fai_n13938013&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Gordon_Brown"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
